As, O what a poor slave did I hold the man of a tender conscience to be! yea, how did I applaud my self for being zeallesse, and fearlesse; together with my great discretion, and moderation: when I saw this man vexed for his zeal, that other hated for his knowledg, a third persecuted for the profession of his Faith, &c. For (being like Cain, Ishmael, Eliab, Michol, Pharaoh, and Festus, I thought their Religion Puritanisme, their conscience of sin, hypocrisie; their profession,
